      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LEKTRA JIMMY (6) was strongly supported last start when a short priced favourite and duly saluted winning by 3.5 lengths at this track in a handy 25.46. Awkwardly drawn but goes well over this trip. Ran the fastest time on the program in his latest win. Well placed and will be tough to beat. SHE REBEL (1) had been racing in honest fashion recording two placings in a row before finishing fifth (24.16) at Bendigo latest. Solid record here winning three races. Likely to play a prominent role. REUBEN HILL (7) was safely held last time out, finishing sixth at Sandown over 515m behind Crackerjack Hops (30.50) in a Grade 5. Expected to feature in the finish. BUSH BIG SHOW (2) flew the lids and led all the way last time. Must be respected.",
